xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.fielddat: Heap memory used by Fielddata (e.g., global ordinals or explicitly enabled fielddata on text fields). This is for the same shards, but not a part of Lucene Total.
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.fixedBit: Heap memory used by Fixed Bit Sets (e.g., deeply nested documents). This is a part of Lucene Total.
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.gcDurati: Time spent performing old Garbage Collections.
Time spent performing young Garbage Collections.
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.indexMem: Heap memory used by Query Cache (e.g., cached filters). This is for the same shards, but not a part of Lucene Total.
Total heap memory used by Lucene for current index. This is the sum of other fields for primary and replica shards on this node.
Total heap memory used by Lucene for current index. This is the sum of other fields for primary and replica shards on this node.
Total heap memory used by Lucene for current index. This is the sum of other fields for primary and replica shards on this node.
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.indexThr: Amount of time spent with index throttling, which indicates slow merging.
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.indexWri: Heap memory used by the Index Writer. This is NOT a part of Lucene Total.
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.indexing: Number of search operations that have been rejected, which occurs when the queue is full.
Number of index, bulk, and write operations in the queue. The bulk threadpool was renamed to write in 6.3, and the index threadpool is deprecated.
Number of index, bulk, and write operations that have been rejected, which occurs when the queue is full. The bulk threadpool was renamed to write in 6.3, and the index threadpool is deprecated.
Amount of time spent with index throttling, which indicates slow disks on a node.
Amount of time spent on indexing operations.
Total heap available to Elasticsearch running in the JVM.
Total heap used by Elasticsearch running in the JVM.
Average latency for indexing documents, which is time it takes to index documents divided by number that were indexed. This considers any shard located on this node, including replicas.
Average latency for searching, which is time it takes to execute searches divided by number of searches submitted. This considers primary and replica shards.
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.luceneTo: Total heap memory used by Lucene for current index. This is the sum of other fields for primary and replica shards on this node.
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.mergeRat: Amount in bytes of merged segments. Larger numbers indicate heavier disk activity.
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.normsDes: Heap memory used by Norms (normalization factors for query-time, text scoring). This is a part of Lucene Total.
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.pointsDe: Heap memory used by Points (e.g., numbers, IPs, and geo data). This is a part of Lucene Total.
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.readThre: Number of GET operations in the queue.
Number of GET operations that have been rejected, which occurs when the queue is full.
Number of search operations in the queue (e.g., shard level searches).
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.requestC: Heap memory used by Request Cache (e.g., instant aggregations). This is for the same shards, but not a part of Lucene Total.
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.searchRa: Number of search requests being executed across primary and replica shards. A single search can run against multiple shards!
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.segmentC: Maximum segment count for primary and replica shards on this node.
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.storedFi: Heap memory used by Stored Fields (e.g., _source). This is a part of Lucene Total.
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.systemLo: Load average over the last minute.
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.termVect: Heap memory used by Term Vectors. This is a part of Lucene Total.
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.termsDes: Heap memory used by Terms (e.g., text). This is a part of Lucene Total.
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.threadQu: Number of get operations waiting to be processed on this node.
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.threadsQ: Number of bulk indexing operations waiting to be processed on this node. A single bulk request can create multiple bulk operations.
Number of generic (internal) operations waiting to be processed on this node.
Number of non-bulk, index operations waiting to be processed on this node.
Number of management (internal) operations waiting to be processed on this node.
Number of search operations waiting to be processed on this node. A single search request can create multiple search operations.
Number of Watcher operations waiting to be processed on this node.

Generic (internal) rejections. These occur when the queue is full.
Get rejections. These occur when the queue is full.
Index rejections. These occur when the queue is full. You should look at bulk indexing.
Get (internal) rejections. These occur when the queue is full.

xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.totalIoW: Total Write I/O. (This metric is not supported on all platforms and may display N/A if I/O data is unavailable.)
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.totalRef: Time spent on Elasticsearch refresh for primary and replica shards.
xpack.monitoring.metrics.esNode.versionM: Heap memory used by Versioning (e.g., updates and deletes). This is NOT a part of Lucene Total.
